> **Status: this is the original handoff/plan (history).** For HOW the system is
> actually built (as-built) + the clone guide, read **[ARCHITECTURE.md](ARCHITECTURE.md)**,
> which is the source of truth and wins where this plan differs.

### ⛔ HARD RULE #0 — NO STRING/REGEX CLASSIFICATION OR RELEVANCE ON FREE TEXT

Burned in production (2026-06-17): `migration_loop._human_messages` gated which
reply threads reached the LLM with `if "MrCall cambia" in subject`. Customers
who confirmed by replying to the *reminder* (subject "…cambia il tuo numero
MrCall", which does not contain the substring "MrCall cambia") were silently
dropped → left `state=sent` → **re-reminded after they had already confirmed.**

The rule, absolute:
- **Reply RELEVANCE** is decided ONLY by structured signals: sender
  (`from:<customer>`), recipient, thread membership, and **date > our send**.
  NEVER by a substring of the subject or body.
- **Reply CLASSIFICATION** (confirm / reschedule / question / autoresponder /
  other) is decided by the LLM reading the actual content — with **structured
  output (tool_use / a schema)**, not by string-matching the model's answer,
  and not by keyword lists (no `AUTO_MARKERS`, no `"ok" in text`).
- Regex is allowed ONLY on genuinely structured input (E.164 phone, git/kubectl
  commands, our own generated markdown). NOT on email subjects/bodies/LLM prose.
- (History) the original `migration_loop.py` violated this at ~154/~165/~188;
  the live file on `main` was fixed in `a93e172` and the operator build does not
  reintroduce it. The as-built statement of this rule lives in ARCHITECTURE.md.

