## 0. What {{ company_name }} IS (mental model — internalize this)

`{{ company_name }}` (`~/{{ company_slug }}-cs`, GitHub private `hahnbanach/{{ company_slug }}-cs`)
is a **CLI front-end / brain for the {{ accounts_default }} operator**. The
**body is the mrcall-desktop engine** (a long-running daemon on this host);
cs drives it. The engine holds months of synced mail, entity memory, a
writing voice trained on {{ accounts_default }}'s own sent mail, tasks, and the
draft/compose/send machinery.

**THREE HARD invariants (do not violate):**

1. **Identity is ALWAYS `{{ email_address }}`.** Every read, draft, send, SMS
   acts as {{ accounts_default }}. Enforced **structurally**, not by prompt discipline: the
   engine daemon gates `token.sub == OWNER_ID`, and cs-SMTP logs in with
   {{ accounts_default }}'s own credentials. No code path can send as anyone else.
2. **cs is a FRONTEND of mrcall-desktop. Free-form / contextual generation
   (replies to customers, anything needing memory+voice+threading) MUST go
   through the engine** (`chat.send` / compose), not cs-local code. cs-local
   SMTP is allowed ONLY for **fixed-template bulk** (e.g. the migration
   reminder) where the engine would only rewrite/distort exact text.
3. **Graduated autonomy is a switch, per send-class (§0.5).** Free-form engine
   replies are **draft-first now** (`CS_TRIAGE_MODE=draft`); fixed-template
   campaign bulk is **autonomous now** under `RATE_CAP` + the `CS_PAUSE`
   kill-switch. The autonomous path is **built now, gated** — moving from draft
   to auto-send later is a config flip, not a rewrite.

State lives in the **engine DB** (SQLite, per-profile), never in repo files.
That is a deliberate, liked property — keep it.

