## 0.5 GRADUATED AUTONOMY — `CS_TRIAGE_MODE` + `CS_PAUSE` (read this twice)

Mario: "*inizia con le bozze, andremo verso l'autonomo.*" NOT draft-only forever,
NOT full-auto now. Autonomy is granted **per send-class**, and the riskiest
class (free-form replies to customers) starts behind a draft gate.

| Send-class | Path | Autonomy NOW |
|---|---|---|
| **Free-form reply** (triage answer, campaign confirm-ack) | engine compose (memory+voice+threading) | **DRAFT** — `CS_TRIAGE_MODE=draft` (default) → engine `create_draft` into {{ email_address }}/Bozze; Mario reviews & sends. |
| **Fixed-template campaign bulk** (reminder, SMS) | cs-SMTP / MrCall SMS proxy, exact text | **AUTONOMOUS** — pre-authorized; gated only by `RATE_CAP` + `CS_PAUSE`. |

- **`CS_TRIAGE_MODE` (default `draft`)** governs every **free-form engine send**
  (triage answers AND campaign confirm-acks). A skill that composes a free-form
  reply consults it: `draft` → compose via `cs chat …` WITHOUT `--allow
  send_email` (engine stores a draft); `send` → with `--allow send_email`. The
  conditional is built into the skill, so flipping `draft→send` is the ONLY
  change — no rewrite.
- **Why draft-first for free-form:** in headless there is no human to approve
  the engine's send gate; auto-sending free-form customer replies with nobody
  in the loop is the v1 burn. **Before EVER setting `CS_TRIAGE_MODE=send`** we
  design a **confidence + scope gate** (auto-send only clearly in-scope/routine;
  everything else stays draft+escalate), on top of `RATE_CAP`, the trained
  voice / `USER_NOTES`, and the kill-switch. Flipping it is a §9 stop-and-ask.
- **`CS_PAUSE`** — if `~/.{{ company_slug }}-cs/CS_PAUSE` exists, the wrapper logs "paused"
  and exits 0. One-touch global kill-switch, no crontab edit (§5).
- **Rollout safety at launch:** triage is in draft mode and the migration
campaign is EXCLUDED (§1). The one live non-migration campaign
(`pilot-2026-06`, §1) has **no pending sends** — its 8 drafts were already sent
by Mario, so the operator's first pass merely **reconciles** them to `sent`
(Sent-archive dedup, §2.5) and starts reply-handling. → **On day one the
operator auto-sends NOTHING free-form to customers.** Autonomy widens only as
Mario flips switches / adds campaigns.

