## 2.5 TWO CAMPAIGN LIFECYCLES (`policy.kind`) — the live env has both

`/campaign-tick` is general only if it handles BOTH live shapes. ⚠️ The engine
`campaigns` row has only `name`+`brief` — **no `policy`/`kind` column** (verified
in `campaign_actions.py`; adding one is an out-of-scope engine change). So
**infer the kind from contact shape**: contacts carrying `draft_subject`/
`draft_body` → composed-draft; else fixed-template. Keep any per-campaign tuning
cs-side, keyed by campaign name. Engine reality the verbs build on: contact
states `drafted|approved|sent|replied|bounced|skipped`; settable contact fields
`…,dossier,draft_subject,draft_body,state,message_id` (store `thread_id` +
day-guards INSIDE `dossier`); `update_contact(state="sent")` stamps `sent_at`
server-side; **no campaign RPC ever SENDS** — sending is cs's job. The two kinds:

**`kind:"fixed-template"` — the migration shape.** Contacts in `sent`; follow-up
= reminders (after Italian noon, capped) + evening SMS; replies classified
(confirm/reschedule/question/autoresponder). Autonomous bulk under
`RATE_CAP`+`CS_PAUSE`. *(The migration is the only such campaign and is EXCLUDED
from the new operator — §1 — so this path serves FUTURE fixed-template
campaigns.)*

**`kind:"composed-draft"` — the pilot/outreach shape** (`pilot-2026-06`).
Contacts in `drafted` carry `draft_subject`/`draft_body` — a personalized
AI-composed mail already written. Per contact:
1. **DEDUP FIRST against the Sent archive** (`cs contacted <email>`) — the Sent
   archive is the dedup truth, NOT the campaign state, which is **stale**: Mario
   sent all 8 pilot drafts **by hand in Gmail** on 2026-06-15, yet the rows still
   say `drafted`/`sent_at:null` (verified `cs contacted info@icoa.it` → sent
   13:33). So:
   - already sent → **reconcile**: mark `sent`, record `thread_id`, **NEVER
     re-send**;
   - genuinely unsent → real pending outreach → **send the composed draft under
     `CS_TRIAGE_MODE`** (draft now = surface for Mario's per-draft review & send;
     `send` later = auto-send), cs-SMTP, cc {{ email_address }}, IMAP-APPEND to Sent so it
     threads + dedups next time.
2. once `sent`, handle the reply (free-form re-engagement: interested/question →
   reply via the engine under `CS_TRIAGE_MODE`; not-interested → mark/close;
   ambiguous → escalate). Never re-send the initial mail.

The **composed-draft SEND is `CS_TRIAGE_MODE`-gated** (personalized free-form
content), NOT autonomous like a fixed-template reminder. The **Sent-archive dedup
is the load-bearing safety net** — it stops the operator re-mailing customers
Mario already wrote to (by hand or otherwise).

