## 3. WHAT TO BUILD (in the `cs-operator` worktree)

### 3a. Granular deterministic Python verbs (extend `cs/cli.py`)
Add a `campaign` verb group the skills call (JSON output). **Put shared logic in
NEW modules `cs/_time.py` (Europe/Rome via `zoneinfo`, DST-correct) and
`cs/campaign.py`, and refactor `migration_loop` to import FROM them** — so the
migration module is retirable after cutover (#9b). Reuse
`cs/migration_mail.build_reminder` + `cs/send_mail.send`.

Cross-cutting rules for every send-verb:
- **stamp-before-send** (#4): write the per-day guard (`last_reminder_sent_day`
  / `last_sms_sent_day`) BEFORE the irreversible send — at-most-once for
  customer-visible (a rare missed send beats a double-billed SMS / duplicate
  mail). `send_mail.send` already raises on SMTP failure; do not stamp on a
  raised send.
- time via `cs/_time.py`, never a hardcoded UTC offset (#5).
- **global daily `RATE_CAP`** across the campaign + **`CS_PAUSE`** check, both
  BEFORE any send; on cap → stop + log, never partial-blast (#7).
- reply located generically: `from:<customer> folder:inbox` + thread date > our
  send; do NOT filter by subject, do NOT exclude on the thread's latest sender
  (#2, #9a). Anchor on the per-contact `thread_id` stored at send time.

Verbs:
- `cs campaign list` → campaigns + per-state counts.
- `cs campaign pending [--name N] --json` → per `sent` contact: flags
  `reply_to_handle` / `reminder_due` / `sms_due`, plus `contact_id`, `email`,
  the reply `thread_id` anchor, and a **SHORT excerpt only — NEVER full customer
  bodies** (PII; #8). Data only, sends nothing. The Opus skill reads the full
  body transiently via `cs rpc emails.list_by_thread` when it classifies.
- `cs campaign send-reminder <contact_id>` → **autonomous fixed-template**:
  RATE_CAP+CS_PAUSE check, stamp `last_reminder_sent_day`+`reminders+1`, THEN
  cs-SMTP reminder (`build_reminder` + `send_mail.send`, cc {{ email_address }}).
- `cs campaign send-sms <contact_id>` → **autonomous fixed-template**: same
  gating, stamp `last_sms_sent_day`+`sms_count+1`, THEN MrCall proxy SMS. On
  failure the skill may fall back to `send-reminder`.
- `cs campaign mark <contact_id> --state X [--confirm] [--escalate] [--note ..]`.
- **Free-form replies do NOT get a campaign verb** — they go through `cs chat
  "…"` (engine compose), draft-or-send per `CS_TRIAGE_MODE` (§0.5). Used by both
  triage answers and the campaign confirm-ack.

`migration_loop.run()` stays importable and **owned by the legacy cron**; the
new verbs do not call it and the new cron does not run it. (FUTURE, not now: a
deterministic `cs campaign tick` orchestrator — see §2 memory note.)

### 3b. Skills (`{{ company_slug }}-cs/.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`)
House style = the existing `.claude/commands/munchausen.md`: silent steps, exact
commands, escalation slots.

- **`cs-operator`** — bootstrap. States the {{ email_address }} identity invariant, checks
