## 5. HEADLESS CRON + PERMISSIONS

- CLI: `claude` at `~/.local/bin/claude` (v2.1.170), authed for the operator user.
  Headless: `claude -p "/cs-operator"` (prints, exits).
- **Permissions:** headless cannot answer prompts. Create a scoped
  `~/.claude/settings.json` (or project `.claude/settings.local.json`) allow-list
  covering exactly the Bash the skills run — the cs venv python
  (`~/{{ company_slug }}-cs/.venv/bin/python -m cs …`) and nothing destructive.
  At `CS_TRIAGE_MODE=draft` the skills never pass `--allow send_email` for
  free-form, so the allow-list need NOT grant autonomous engine sends (by
design). Verify a run neither halts on a prompt nor gets blanket powers.
  Prefer `--allowedTools`/settings over `--dangerously-skip-permissions`.
- **Wrapper** `cs/scripts/cs_operator_cron.sh`:
  - `cd` into the deployed working tree (after `cs-operator` merges to `main`, §7);
  - if `~/.{{ company_slug }}-cs/CS_PAUSE` exists → log "paused", exit 0 (kill-switch);
  - **`flock`** `~/.{{ company_slug }}-cs/cs_operator.lock` (non-blocking) so a slow/hung run
    never overlaps the next 2h tick against the engine;
  - then `exec claude -p "/cs-operator" <flags>`; log to
    `~/.{{ company_slug }}-cs/cs_operator.log` (IDs/actions only — #11).
